# Adding Tools to Aura

## Tool file pattern

```typescript
import { tool } from "ai";
import { z } from "zod";

export function createMyTools() {
  return {
    my_tool: tool({
      description: "Clear description of what this does and when to use it.",
      inputSchema: z.object({
        param: z.string().describe("What this parameter is"),
      }),
      execute: async ({ param }) => {
        try {
          // ... implementation
          logger.info("my_tool called", { param });
          return { ok: true, result: "..." };
        } catch (error: any) {
          logger.error("my_tool failed", { error: error.message });
          return { ok: false, error: `Failed: ${error.message}` };
        }
      },
    }),
  };
}
```

## Checklist for new tools

1. Create tool in `src/tools/` (new file or existing)
2. Use `inputSchema` (NOT `parameters`) -- AI SDK v6
3. Return `{ ok: true, ... }` on success, `{ ok: false, error: "..." }` on failure
4. Log with `logger.info` / `logger.error`
5. Add `await throttle()` before any Slack API calls
6. Spread into `createSlackTools` in `src/tools/slack.ts`
7. Add to the tools list in `src/personality/system-prompt.ts`
8. Add usage guidance in the system prompt
9. Document any new Slack scopes needed in README
